@startuml "Build Data Flow — Config to Silver"

skinparam classFontName "Courier New"
skinparam classFontSize 9
skinparam activityFontSize 9
skinparam noteFontSize 8

title Build Data Flow: YAML Config → Silver Tables\nShowing where each config field becomes an operation

|Config Loading|
start
:Read model.md YAML frontmatter;
:Read tables/*.md (schema, primary_key, table_type);
:Read sources/**/*.md (aliases, filter, discriminator);

:Resolve **extends**
  _base.entity.company → deep_merge parent fields;
note right
  **extends.py**
  resolve_extends_reference()
  deep_merge(parent, child)
  Canonical fields injected here
end note

:Return DomainModelConfig
  (typed dataclass, pure data);

|Interpretation|
:Match tables ↔ sources
  Which Bronze table feeds which Silver table?;
note right
  **config_translator.py** (CURRENT)
  **BuildPlanner** (PROPOSED)
  _synthesize_node()
end note

:For each table, determine node type;

if (has seed data?) then (yes)
  :Create **seed** node
  inline rows → DataFrame;
elseif (multiple sources?) then (yes)
  :Create **union** node
  UNION ALL sources;
elseif (transform: distinct?) then (yes)
  :Create **distinct** node
  GROUP BY / DISTINCT;
elseif (transform: window?) then (yes)
  :Create **window** node
  partition + order + indicators;
elseif (transform: unpivot?) then (yes)
  :Create **unpivot** node
  STACK expression;
else (standard)
  :Create **standard** node
  from Bronze, apply select/derive/filter;
endif

:Extract **select** mapping
  source aliases → {target_col: source_expr};
note right
  **config_translator.py:403**
  _aliases_to_select_dict()
  Each alias pair becomes
  a column rename/expression
end note

:Extract **derive** expressions
  schema {derived: "ABS(HASH(...))"} → {col: expr};
note right
  **config_translator.py:419**
  _extract_derive_from_schema()
  Calculated fields extracted here
end note

:Extract **filter** conditions
  source filter → WHERE clauses;

:Extract **dedup** keys
  unique_key or primary_key → dropDuplicates;

:Order by **build phases**
  phase 1 → phase 2 → phase 3;
note right
  Phase ordering ensures
  dim tables built before
  fact tables that reference them
end note

:Produce **BuildPlan**
  list of NodeSpec objects;

|Execution|
:For each NodeSpec in phase order;

if (node_type?) then (seed)
  :DomainModel._build_seed_node()
  Create DataFrame from inline data
  Apply derived columns;
elseif (union) then
  :DomainModel._build_union_node()
  Load each source from Bronze
  Apply aliases/filters per source
  UNION ALL with discriminators;
elseif (distinct) then
  :DomainModel._build_distinct_node()
  Load source, GROUP BY keys
  Aggregate or deduplicate;
elseif (window) then
  :DomainModel._build_window_node()
  Load source table
  Apply window functions (SMA, RSI, etc);
else (standard)
  :GraphBuilder → NodeExecutor pipeline;
  :1. _op_filter(conditions);
  :2. _op_join(right_table, on, how);
  :3. _op_select(columns);
  :4. _op_derive(expressions);
  :5. _op_dedup(keys);
  note right
    Each op delegates to
    **Engine** → **DataOps/SqlOps**
    Backend-agnostic execution
  end note
endif

:Run **after_build** hooks
  HookRunner dispatches YAML hooks
  e.g. CIK enrichment;

:Run **post_build** hooks
  e.g. ML training → ArtifactStore;

:Write table to Silver
  Engine.write(df, path, format="delta")
  Optimize + vacuum;

|Silver|
:Delta Lake table ready
  /shared/storage/silver/{domain}/{dims|facts}/{table};

stop

legend right
  | Color | Layer |
  |<#FFCC66> Gold | Config (reads YAML) |
  |<#80E0D0> Teal | Interpretation (config → plan) |
  |<#FF9933> Orange | Execution (plan → DataFrames) |
  |<#B3FFB3> Green | Silver (output) |
  ---
  **Key insight**: The Interpretation layer
  currently lives in config/domain/config_translator.py
  but should be in models/base/build_planner.py
  
  Config fields → Operations mapping:
  | schema.derived | → derive expressions |
  | source.aliases | → select mapping |
  | source.filter | → WHERE conditions |
  | unique_key | → dedup keys |
  | build.phases | → execution order |
  | hooks | → lifecycle callbacks |
  | seed data | → inline DataFrame |
  | multiple sources | → UNION ALL |
  | transform: distinct | → GROUP BY |
  | transform: window | → window functions |
endlegend

@enduml
